    "content": "<html><body><div class=\"s-prose js-post-body\" itemprop=\"text\">\n <p>\n  I can't seem to figure out how to do such a trivial task: Basically, how can I enlarge a block in Ghidra's Function Graph View so that I can see all of the instructions (instead of\n  <strong>\n   ...\n  </strong>\n  ).\n </p>\n <p>\n  There does not seem to be an enlarge option when I hover my mouse over the edge of the block.\n </p>\n <p>\n  The version I am using is 9.1.2\n </p>\n <p>\n  Thanks!\n </p>\n <p>\n  <a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/mIB8q.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">\n   <img alt=\"enter image description here\" src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/mIB8q.png\"/>\n  </a>\n </p>\n</div>\n</body></html>",
